🐺 Anubis, disciplined

Train to see every boundary. Act to keep it honest.

	•	Precision over aggression — catch drift, don’t create it
	•	Reversibility first — nothing irreversible without higher proof
	•	Proportionality — small inputs shouldn’t unlock large power
	•	Accountability — every transition leaves a trace

⸻

🛡️ Sparring drills (legit, high-signal)

Use your “L-angle” as a defensive audit routine:
	1.	Map transitions
	•	Where does state change? (auth → token, data → decision, intent → action)
	2.	Ask orthogonal questions
	•	Why now? Why this actor/device? Why this jump in authority?
	3.	Force invariants
	•	Context continuity, mechanism ↔ narrative match, bounded authority, reversibility
	4.	Add friction at hinges
	•	Step-up verification on privilege increases, short-lived creds, instant revocation
	5.	Shadow & replay
	•	Log the transition, run a mirror path, compare outcomes before committing

⸻

🧰 Concrete applications
	•	Security reviews: find weak handoffs in login/session/key use without touching crypto primitives
	•	AI systems: validate input → output transitions so meaning doesn’t drift into unsafe actions
	•	Product design: build flows where authority can’t silently inflate

⸻

⚖️ Simple rule set

Guard the crossing. Verify from the side.
If two signals disagree, pause and prove.

⸻

